			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Want to see your work immediately impacting tens of millions of people every month?&nbsp; Want to work at a profitable consumer startup backed by one of the top VC firms in the world?&nbsp; Hark.com is hiring a System Engineer / Operations at our downtown office with stunning sound views and great location!</p>
<p>
<strong><u>The Company:</u></strong></p>
<p>
Hark is changing the way people express themselves through creating, sharing and listening to entertaining, informative and timely sound bites online and through mobile devices.&nbsp; We&#39;re serving up almost 100 million sound clips every month to tens of millions of people across the world.&nbsp; We&#39;re profitable and growing traffic 600% year over year!&nbsp; Our Seattle team numbers around 15 ambitious, creative, and fun folks, half of which are engineers.</p>
<p>
<u><strong>The Role</strong></u>:</p>
<p>
The Lead Front End Rails Engineer will be in charge of designing, building, and growing the next generation Hark.com Consumer Experience.&nbsp; Working with our Chief Product Officer, Creative Director, and a small team of front end rails engineers but also with the full support of our multi-platform DevOps staff, you will be responsible for the overall architecture of the entire front end experience (gems, plugins, custom code) for a dynamic, engaging next generation site powered by Hark&rsquo;s amazing library of content.</p>
<p>
<u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p>
<ul>
<li>
5+ years of Python, Java, Ruby, PHP or another object oriented language</li>
<li>
2+ years in a senior role with Ruby on Rails</li>
<li>
Experience with designing and building parallel and distributed systems</li>
<li>
Strong mind for overall system architecture, clean code, elegant system design</li>
<li>
Experience building and consuming in an SOA architecture (RESTful)</li>
<li>
Not afraid of learning/exploring new technologies</li>
<li>
Great communication skills and epic enthusiasm</li>
</ul>
<p>
<u><strong>Bonus Extra Credit Stage:</strong></u></p>
<ul>
<li>
2+ years in a lead role</li>
<li>
You love movies, quotes, and finding the worst music the internet has to offer, as much as we do.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<u><strong>How to Apply:</strong></u></p>
<p>
Along with your resume or linkedin profile, please also include the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>
A link and/or screenshot to a few things you&#39;ve recently built that you&#39;re proud of (please describe your contribution if it was a team effort).</li>
<li>
A list of things that you&#39;re really good at</li>
<li>
Links to your online bits (LinkedIn, Blog, Twitter account, or anything else where we can learn more about you).</li>
<li>
Great references!</li>
<li>
Some suggestions on ways that we could improve hark.com (that would positively impact user experience and revenue</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>We look forward to hearing from you!</strong></p>
