<p>
Hark is changing the way people express themselves through creating, sharing and listening to entertaining, informative and timely sound bites online and through mobile devices.&nbsp; We&#39;re serving up almost 100 million sound clips every month to tens of millions of people across the world.&nbsp; We&#39;re profitable and growing traffic 600% year over year!&nbsp; Our Seattle team numbers around 15 ambitious, creative, and fun folks, half of which are engineers.</p>
<p>
<strong><u>The Role:</u></strong></p>
<p>
The Sr. Product Manager - Mobile/API will own and drive the vision of the API and Mobile products.&nbsp; From working with stakeholders to understand all requirements and use cases, to driving through execution with the development team, you will be responsible for end to end ownership of two crucial areas of the product.</p>
<p>
This role provides a broad range of experiences &ndash; both working with the intricacies of an API as well as working closely with the design team to deliver the full end to end user experience of the mobile app.&nbsp; If you&rsquo;re looking for a role that lets you wear multiple hats, this is it!</p>
<p>
<strong><u>Requirements:</u></strong></p>
<p>
&bull; 5+ years as a product manager<br />
&bull; 3+ years working on consumer facing web sites<br />
&bull; Experience shipping mobile products<br />
&bull; Experience with agile development practices<br />
&bull; API experience is a plus<br />
&bull; A very high degree of intellectual curiosity<br />
&bull; Highly creative, independent and motivated to go out and change the world!</p>
